what are the symptoms of colitis can somebody tell me the symtoms of colitis my sister has been dignose with it is it bad colitis is inflammation of the colon it can be due to a number of causes including infections poor blood supply ischemic colitis medications adderall and even nsaids and immunologic diseases ulcerative colitis and crohn's colitis people used to call irritable bowel syndrome ibs spastic colitis which is misleading the chief symptom is diarrhea when the rectum is involved there can also be a sensation of incomplete evacuation after bowel movements called tenesmus the diarrhea can be bloody or non bloody typically diarrhea persists during both day and night for diagnosis stool studies and usually a colonoscopy or sigmoidoscopy with biopsies are necessary occasionally people who are really sick may also need abdominal x rays and ct scans of the abdomen and pelvis Irritable bowel syndrome Colorectal cancer Coeliac disease Inflammatory bowel disease Hemorrhoid Diverticulitis Colonoscopy Abdominal pain Fecal incontinence Stomach cancer Cancer Autistic enterocolitis Constipation Diverticulosis Prostate cancer Folic acid Ovarian cancer Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Endometriosis Pneumonia Chronic fatigue syndrome Urinary incontinence Sulfasalazine Sigmoidoscopy Clostridium difficile Hirschsprung's disease Gastroenteritis Autoimmune diseases Appendicitis Food allergy Gastroesophageal reflux disease Ileostomy Hepatitis Group A streptococcal infection Aortic dissection Barium enema Campylobacteriosis Bowel obstruction Endometrial cancer Multiple sclerosis Hypoglycemia Cirrhosis Hepatitis C Escherichia coli O157:H7 Diabetes mellitus Rheumatoid arthritis Traumatic brain injury Fistula Medicine Stroke Hodgkin's lymphoma Gonorrhoea Reiter's syndrome Vomiting Glycogen storage disease type I Schistosomiasis Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Familial adenomatous polyposis Multiple chemical sensitivity IgA nephropathy Beh__et's disease Esophageal cancer Esophagogast